result.execSummary:
The defendant Amber M Tuckwab was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Amber M Tuckwab in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Defendant Amber M Tuckwab in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:00 PM. Called 16CM85, 16CF33 and 16CF131. 16CF33 is SEHR and other two matters are PLEAS. State - 16CM85 - plead g/nc to counts #2 and #3 as alleged, counts #1 and #4 - DRI, joint recommendnation of 30 days jail on both counts #2 and #3 -  concurrent to each other, court costs on each count. State - 16CF131 - plead G to counts #2, #3, #6 and#7 as alleged, counts #1, #4 and #5 - DRI, joint recommendation on counts #2, #6 and #7 - 120 days jail on each count - concurrent to each other and to jail time on 16CM85, court costs on each count, on count #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years - consecutive to all jail times, with conditons of $300 fine plus costs, AODA and follow thru, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, employment/school, 200 hours of community service. Joy and Tuckwab agree. Court explains DRI to defendant. Court - 16CM85 - dismisses and reads in counts #1 and #4. Tuckwab pleads G to counts #2 and #3 on 16CM85; Court - 16CF131 - dismiss and reads in counts #1, #4 and #5. Tuckwab pleads G to counts #2, #3, #6 and #7 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts pleas, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Joy makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Tuckwab withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 16CM85 - counts #2 and #3 - 30 days in FC jail - concurrent to each other - huber and good time allowed - credit from 8/3/16 (credit for 30 days), court costs on each count - due 60 days after release from custody/CO (should be released today); 16CF131 - counts #2, #6 and #7 - 120 days in FC jail on each count - concurrent to each other and to jail on 16CM85 - huber and good time allowed - credit from 6/19/16 (credit for 120 days); court costs on each count - due 60 days after release from custody/CO (should be released today); count #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years - consecutive to jail time on 16CM85 and other counts on 16CF131 - with conditions of: $300 fine plus costs - 60 days after release from incarceration/CO (should be released today), AODA and follow thru, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 200 hours of community service - to be performed within the first year of probation, submit DNA sample, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, right to appeal. 16CF33 - both counsel have sentencing after revocation paperwork, no inaccuracies. State makes final argument prior to recommendations - recommends on both counts (#2 and #3) - 164 days credit. Joy makes final argument prior to recommendations - recommends 164 days on both counts. Tuckwab withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following - both counts #2 and #3 - 164 days jail on each count, concurrent to each other and concurrent to jail time imposed on 16CF131 and 16CM85, with 164 days credit, turn any unpaid fines into civil judgments, right to appeal, adjourned.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 30, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
